reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for the price in today's market!
reviews.reviewText: This GPU isn't the top of the line, but paired with my 60hz 2560x1600 HP monitor, it's given me crystal clear images with good FPS in Halo Infinite (@1366x768 for H.I. only), Kerbal Space Program, and Automation, the Car Company Tycoon Game. Though in Beam.NG, visual settings have to be set to Low for decent-good FPS. It keeps at a decent temperature (35-45°C) while being run at 100% consistently. If you're looking for a good GPU for 3D dense programs such as Second Life, this one is more then capable with the sacrifice of FPS (25-30 at High, 10-15 at Ultra graphics settings).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for old computers
reviews.reviewText: Previously I tried to get a Radeon RX580 to work with my old Dell T3400 workstation PC. After fighting with the AMD drivers for over a few days I gave up and returned the AMD product. I had high hopes looking for an old GPU to put into my T3400. Just so I can play my 4K videos I edit. All videos are made on my Pixel6 phone in 4K but my old PC could not edit nor play back any 4K videos. Just out of impulse, I decided to try the GT1030 4gig card and installed in 5 minutes and after Windows 10 updated the Driver, I downloaded the driver from NVidia for the latest update driver. My old PC has gained a new life. Well at least for the time being. This old Dell T3400 can finally play my 4K videos. This will become my backup PC once I get my 12th Gen Intel I7 PC running this month with a RTX 4070. Very happy with my impulse buy of just about $100. To give my old PC some more life. It replaced a 2gig GT710 GPU.
